<div class="container" style="padding:40px 0;">
  <div style="max-width:600px;margin:0 auto;">
    <div class="section-title">
      <h2>📦 Software Integrity Lab</h2>
      <p class="subtitle">A08: Software & Data Integrity Failures</p>
      <div class="accent-line"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="alert alert-warning">
      🎯 <strong>Integrity Failures Lab:</strong> This simulates installing packages without verifying their integrity. In real scenarios, attackers can publish malicious packages to steal credentials!
    </div>

    <div class="card" style="padding:24px;margin-bottom:20px;">
      <h3 style="margin-bottom:16px;">Install a Package (Simulated)</h3>
      <form action="/integrity/install" method="POST">
        <div class="form-group">
          <label class="form-label">Package Name</label>
          <input type="text" name="package_name" class="form-input" placeholder="e.g., avengers-utils" value="malicious-package-v1.0.0">
        </div>
        <div class="form-divider" style="text-align:center;color:var(--text-dim);margin:16px 0;">— or —</div>
        <div class="form-group">
          <label class="form-label">Package URL</label>
          <input type="text" name="package_url" class="form-input" placeholder="https://evil-npm-registry.com/package.tgz">
        </div>
        <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg" style="width:100%;">📦 Install Package</button>
      </form>
    </div>

    <% if (result) { %>
      <div class="card" style="padding:24px;border-color:var(--warning);">
        <h4 style="color:var(--warning);margin-bottom:12px;">⚠️ Installation Result</h4>
        <pre><%= result %></pre>
      </div>
    <% } %>

    <div class="card" style="padding:24px;margin-top:20px;">
      <h4 style="margin-bottom:12px;">💡 What's the vulnerability?</h4>
      <p style="color:var(--text-muted);font-size:0.9rem;line-height:1.7;">
        <strong>A08: Software and Data Integrity Failures</strong> occurs when software is installed without verifying its integrity through checksums, signatures, or trusted sources. Attackers can:
      </p>
      <ul style="color:var(--text-muted);font-size:0.85rem;line-height:1.8;padding-left:20px;margin-top:10px;">
        <li>Publish malicious packages with similar names (typosquatting)</li>
        <li>Compromise legitimate packages and add backdoors</li>
        <li>Use man-in-the-middle attacks to replace packages during download</li>
        <li>Exploit CI/CD pipelines that don't verify package integrity</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
